## 7. Key Decision Point (Critical Insight)

The most important logic in sudo binaries is 

> **The policy decision branch that determines whether execution is allowed**

This is not in `main` alone.

It is typically inside 

* sudoers plugin
* or large fcn blocks (~0x2xxxxâ€“0x3xxxx range)

Your binary shows strong candidates 

* `fcn.0002ede0`
* `fcn.00031310`

These likely contain 

```
if (policy_check(user, command) == ALLOW)
    proceed
else
    deny
```

